ey-mara-guillermo-del-toro-nightmare-alley-bradley-cooper-cate-blanchett-fox-searchlight-1202710574/ Rooney Mara Joins Guillermo Del Toro\u2019s \u2018Nightmare Alley\u2019 At Fox Searchlight]</ref>\n|}\n\n== Stage ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Production\n!scope=\"col\"| Venue\n!scope=\"col\"| Role(s)\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Refs.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=row | 1992\n| ''[[Electra]]''\n| [[National Institute of Dramatic Art]]\n| Electra\n| Directed by [[Lindy Davies]]\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\"newyorker\"/>\n|-\n! scope=row | 1992\n| ''[[Top Girls]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Patient Griselda/Nell/Jeanine\n| First role at the [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/cate-blanchett-9214915#early-career |title=Cate Blanchett |publisher=Biography |accessdate=17 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170419193505/http://www.biography.com/people/cate-blanchett-9214915 |archivedate=19 April 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 1993\n| ''Kafka Dances''\n| [[Griffin Theatre Company]]\n| Bride/Felice\n| From playwright [[Timothy Daly (playwright)|Timothy Daly]]. Production was remounted at the [[Sydney Theatre Company]] the following year.\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n! scope=row | 1993\n| ''[[Oleanna (play)|Oleanna]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Carol\n| Opposite to [[Geoffrey Rush]].\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.sydneytheatre.com.au/magazine/posts/2014/september/archive-cate-blanchett |title=Archive: Cate Blanchett |date=4 September 2014 |publisher=[[Sydney Theatre Company]] |accessdate=17 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317190615/https://www.sydneytheatre.com.au/magazine/posts/2014/september/a