 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315045111/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/28/theater/blanchett-to-make-broadway-debut-in-play-directed-by-john-crowley.html |archivedate=15 March 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 2017\n| ''[[Platonov (play)|The Present]]''\n| [[Ethel Barrymore Theatre]]\n| {{sort|Petrovna|Anna Petrovna}}\n| [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut.\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=Cate Blanchett's Broadway debut in The Present delights critics |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2017/jan/09/cate-blanchett-broadway-debut-the-present-wins-over-critics-chekhov-adaptation |first=Nadia |last=Khomami |work=The Guardian |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=10 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109195303/https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2017/jan/09/cate-blanchett-broadway-debut-the-present-wins-over-critics-chekhov-adaptation |archivedate=9 January 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 2019\n| ''When We Have Sufficiently Tortured Each Other''\n| [[Royal National Theatre]]\n| Woman\n| National Theatre debut. Written by [[Martin Crimp]], directed by [[Katie Mitchell]].\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dickson |first1=Andrew |title=Cate Blanchett on her S&M-themed play: 'I see theatre as a provocation' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2019/jan/09/cate-blanchett-interview-i-think-ive-got-six-months-of-acting-left-when-we-have-sufficiently-tortured-each-other |accessdate=9 January 2019 |work=The Guardian |date=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Year(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Channel\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{abbr|Refs.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=row | 1993\n| ''[[Police Rescue]]''\n| {{sort|Haines|Mrs. Haines}}\n| [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]\n| Television serie