\" />\n|-\n! scope=row | 2006\n| ''[[A Kind of Alaska]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n|\n|Co-director with [[Andrew Upton]] 30 November 2006 \u2212 20 January 2007, Sydney.\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/arts-reviews/reuniona-kind-of-alaska/2006/12/04/1165080847430.html |title=Reunion/A Kind of Alaska |first=Mark |last=Hopkins |work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=4 December 2006 |accessdate=17 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070524101259/http://www.smh.com.au/news/arts-reviews/reuniona-kind-of-alaska/2006/12/04/1165080847430.html |archivedate=24 May 2007 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 2007\n| ''[[Blackbird (play)|Blackbird]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| \n| Directed [[David Harrower]]'s play; 15 December 2007 \u2212 16 February 2008, Sydney;<br>Travelled to New Zealand International Arts Festival, 23 February 2008 \u2212 2 March 2008; Travelled to [[Ruhrfestspiele]] festival, Germany, 8 \u2212 12 May 2008.\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.australianstage.com.au/200805071425/news/sydney/stc-opens-in-germany.html |title=STC opens in Germany |publisher=The Australian Stage |date=7 May 2008 |accessdate=17 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316075024/http://australianstage.com.au/200805071425/news/sydney/stc-opens-in-germany.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 2009\n| [[Shakespearean history#The .22Wars of the Roses.22 cycle|''The War of the Roses'']]\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Richard II/Lady Anne\n| Directed by [[Benedict Andrews]]. Part of the [[Sydney Festival]] 2009\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n! scope=row | 2009\n| ''{{sortname|A|Streetcar Named Desire|A Streetcar Named Desire (play)}}''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| {{sort|DuBois|[[Blanche DuBois]]}}\n| Directed by [[Liv Ullmann]]; opposite [[Joel Edgerton]]; Travelled to [[John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts]] in Washington, D.C., 29 October \u2013 21 November 2009; Travelled to [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]]'s Harvey Theatre, New York, 27 November \u2013 20 December 2009\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Cate Blanchett Before Broadway: 5 Memorable Stage Roles|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/cate-blanchett-before-broadway-5-memorable-stage-roles-963309/item/plenty-blanchett-before-broadway-963304|first=David|last=Rooney|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=13 January 2017|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> \n|-\n! scope=row | 2011\n| ''[[Uncle Vanya]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Yelena\n| Adaptation by [[Andrew Upton]]; opposite [[Richard Roxburgh]], John Bell, and [[Hugo Weaving]]; Travelled to [[John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts]], Washington, D. C., 4\u201327 August 2011; Travelled to [[Lincoln Center]] Festival, New York, 19\u201328 July 2012\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Cate Blanchett Tidies Up for New York Run of Stage Play \"The Maids\" |url=https://variety.com/2014/legit/news/cate-blanchett-tidies-up-for-new-york-run-of-stage-play-the-maids-1201037005/ |work=Variety |date=8 January 2014 |accessdate=17 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305055443/http://variety.com/2014/legit/news/cate-blanchett-tidies-up-for-new-york-run-of-stage-play-the-maids-1201037005/ |archivedate=5 March 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | 2011\n| ''[[Gro\u00df und klein|Gross und Klein]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Lotte\n| Directed by [[Benedict Andrews]]; new translation by [[Martin Crimp]]; co-commissioned by the [[Barbican Centre]]; Travelled to [[2012 Cultural Olympiad#London 2012 Festival|London 2012 Festival]], [[Th\u00e9\u00e2tre de la Ville]], [[Vienna Festival]], and [[Ruhrfestspiele]].\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n! scope=row | 2013\n| ''[[The Maids]]''\n| [[Sydney Theatre Company]]\n| Claire\n| Directed by [[Benedict An