nchett_on_screen_and_stage"}
{"title_page": "Bruno Decc", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian film director and writer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Bruno Decc\n[[File:Bruno_Decc_Arc_2019.jpg||thumb 400 px|right|Bruno Decc speaks at a panel at the III Arc Film Festival in Mainz, Germany]]\n| birth_place     = [[Sao Paulo]], [[Brazil]]\n| nationality      = Brazilian\n| occupation     = Director and Screenwriter\n| credits            = {{unbulleted list| ''Escape from Brazil''| ''Two Signs' Den: Epilogue''| ''Carpe Aeternitatem''| ''Breu''| ''Nootropic''}}\n}}\n\n'''Bruno Decc''' is a Brazilian film director and writer. He studied architecture and urbanism at the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]] and started working on films in 2007.\n\n==Work==\nDecc started as a director, writer, producer and photographer in indie film making and advertising through his production company, Decc Films.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://www.ideafixa.com/oldbutgold/cinema-independente-na-era-dos-editais\n | title = Independent Cinema in the Grant Age\n | last = Trabasso\n | first = Rafael \n | date = October 21, 2015\n | website = Ideafixa.com\n | publisher =\n | access-date =2017-01-09\n | quote = }}</ref> From 2011 to 2018, he worked closely with Maria Farinha Films, producing, writing and directing documentaries, short films and television shows. Since 2019 he's been consulting for Escape Films ASBL in Belgium.\n\nIn 2016, his ninth short film (''Two Signs' Den: Epilogue'') won Best Experimental Film Award<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://www.asff.co.uk/winners-announced-aesthetica-short-film-festival-awards-ceremony-2016/\n | title = Winners Announced: Aesthetica Short Film Festival Awards Ceremony 2016\n | last = \n | first = \n | date = November 7, 2016\n | website = Asff.co.uk\n | publisher =\n | access-date =2017-01-09\n | quote = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://www.asff.co.uk/bruno-decc-experimental-cinema/\n | title = Bruno Decc: Experimental Cinema\n | last = \n | first =  \n | date = December 22, 2016\n | website = Asff.co.uk\n | publisher =\n | access-date =2017-01-09\n | quote = }}</ref> at the VI [[Aesthetica Short Film Festival]], in York, England.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Decc, Bruno}}\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n\n\n{{Brazil-film-director-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian film director and writer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Bruno Decc\n[[File:Bruno_Decc_Arc_2019.jpg||thumb 400 px|right|Bruno Decc speaks at a panel at the III Arc Film Festival in Mainz, Germany]]\n| birth_place     = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], S\u00e3o Paulo, BRA\n| nationality      = Brazilian\n| occupation     = Director and Screenwriter\n| credits            = {{unbulleted list| ''Escape from Brazil''| ''Two Signs' Den: Epilogue''| ''Carpe Aeternitatem''| ''Breu''| ''Nootropic''}}\n}}\n\n'''Bruno Decc''' is a Brazilian film director and writer. He studied architecture and urbanism at the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]] and started working on films in 2007.\n\n==Work==\nDecc started as a director, writer, producer and photographer in indie film making and advertising through his production company, Decc Films.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://www.ideafixa.com/oldbutgold/cinema-independente-na-era-dos-editais\n | title = Independent Cinema in the Grant Age\n | last = Trabasso\n | first = Rafael \n | date = October 21, 2015\n | website = Ideafixa.com\n | publisher =\n | access-date =2017-01-09\n | quote = }}</ref> From 2011 to 2018, he worked closely with Maria Farinha Films, producing, writing and directing documentaries, short films and television shows. Since 2019 he's been consulting for Escape Films ASBL in Belgium.\n\nIn 2016, his ninth short film (''Two Signs' Den: Epilogue'') won Best Experimental Film Award<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://www.asff.co.uk