age = 36.0\n  |change     = +5.8\n}}\n{{Election box majority\n  | |votes = 21,847\n  |percentage = 28.0\n  |change     = -11.6\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n  | |votes = 78,101\n  |percentage = 100\n  |change     = -15.4\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link\n| |winner = Democratic Party (US)\n|swing = -5.8\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin|title=Michigan gubernatorial election, 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mielections.us/election/results/2018GEN_CENR.html|title=2018 Michigan Official General Election Results - 11/06/2018|website=mielections.us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lwvoa.org/files/LWVOAFullVoterGuideNovember2018-compressed.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=November 16, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116173304/http://www.lwvoa.org/files/LWVOAFullVoterGuideNovember2018-compressed.pdf |archive-date=November 16, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link\n |party = Democratic Party (United States)\n |candidate = Gretchen Whitmer<br>[[Garlin Gilchrist]]\n |votes = 2,256,791\n |percentage = 53.34%\n |change = +6.48%\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party = Republican Party (United States)|candidate = [[Bill Schuette]]<br>[[Lisa Posthumus Lyons]]|votes = 1,853,650|percentage = 43.81%|change = -7.11%\n| }}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party = Libertarian Party (United States)|candidate = Bill Gelineau <br>Angelique Chaiser Thomas|votes = 56,752|percentage = 1.34%|change = +0.21%\n| }}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party = Green Party of the United States|candidate = Jennifer V. Kurland<br>Charin H. Davenport|votes = 28,857|percentage = 0.68%|change = +0.21%\n| }}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party = Constitution Party (United States)|candidate = Todd Schleiger<br>Earl P. Lackie|votes = 24,701|percentage = 0.58%|change = -0.03%\n| }}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party = Natural Law Party|candidate = Keith Butkovitch<br>Raymond Warner|votes = 10,258|percentage = 0.24%|change = -\n| }}\n{{Election box majority\n| |votes = 403,141\n |percentage = 9.53%\n |change = +5.47%\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n| |votes = 4,231,009\n |percentage =\n |change = 34.04%\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link\n  | |winner = Democratic Party (US)\n  |loser = Republican Party (US)\n  |swing = \n}}\n{{election box end}}\n\n==Political positions==\n\n===Education===\nWhitmer would like to phase in full-day Universal Pre-K for 4-year-olds in Michigan. She also wants to reduce the cost of childcare for struggling families. She would eliminate Michigan's current 3rd grade \"read or flunk\" policy, which she has said penalizes students who have been failed by the education system, and would instead work to improve their reading skills. She proposes that all high school students be offered two years of debt-free higher education, either college or post-secondary training for skilled trades.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bridgemi.com/public-sector/what-michigan-schools-will-look-under-governor-whitmer-or-schuette|title=What Michigan schools will look like under Governor Whitmer or Schuette|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=October 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Health care===\nWhitmer has said she would fight Republican efforts to take away protections for patients with preexisting conditions. In the State Senate, Whitmer successfully worked to expand Medicaid coverage in the state. She has spoken against single-payer healthcare as unrealistic. She has stated she would work to lower the cost of prescription drugs, and would get rid of Shuette's drug immunity law, which she believes protects drug companies from legal trouble if their drugs harm or kill people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2018/07/18/michigan-governor-race-gretchen-whitmer-blue-cross/|title=A Blue Cross CEO Encouraged a Michigan Woman to Get Into Politics. Now She's Running for Governor and Says Single Payer Is Unrealistic.|last=Jilani|first=Zaid|date=July 18, 2018|website=The Intercept-US|accessdate=October 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Taxation===\nIn March 2019 Whitmer proposed increasing the gasoline tax 45 cents per gallon to fund road repairs. If it is enacted Michigan will have the highest fuel tax in the [[United States]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/news/local/michigan/2019/03/04/whitmer-budget-road-funding-options/3055987002/|title=Gov. Gretchen Whitmer to propose 45-cent hike in fuel tax to fund Michigan roads|website=Detroit Free Press|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWhitmer has two children with her first husband, Gary Shrewsbury. The couple divorced, and in 2011 she married dentist Marc Mallory, who has three children from his previous marriage.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2018/06/27/gretch-whitmer-profile-michigan-governor/698088002/|title=Whitmer rises to establishment choice in Democrats' gov race|work=Detroit News|accessdate=August 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gretchenwhitmer.com/bio/|title=Meet Gretchen \u2013 Gretchen Whitmer for Governor|work=Gretchen Whitmer for Governor|accessdate=August 10, 2018}}</ref> Whitmer and Mallory live in [[East Lansing, Michigan]], with her two daughters, Sherry and Sydney, and his three sons, Alex, Mason, and Winston.<ref name=\"monprofile\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oaklandlegalnews.com/washtenaw/1423164|title=Monday Profile: Gretchen Whitmer|date=April 11, 2016|work=Oakland Legal News|accessdate=December 25, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226060218/http://www.oaklandlegalnews.com/washtenaw/1423164|archive-date=December 26, 2016|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wlns.com/news/6-news-on-demand/skubick-whitmer-family-joins-in-run-for-governor/999903055|title=Skubick: Whitmer family joins in run for governor|last=VanderKolk|first=Kevin|date=January 4, 2017|work=WLNS|accessdate=August 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Gretchen Whitmer}}\n* [https://gretchenwhitmer.com/ Campaign website]\n* [http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=37868 Project Vote Smart \u2013 Senator Gretchen Whitmer (MI)] profile\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060526202257/http://www.michiganliberal.com/tag.do?tag=SD23 Michigan Liberal \u2013 SD23]\n* {{C-SPAN|Gretchen Whitmer}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-mi-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=Laura Baird}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[Michigan House of Representatives]]<br>from the 70th district|years=2001\u20132003}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Judy Emmons]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Michael C. Murphy (Michigan politician)|Michael C. Murphy]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[Michigan House of Representatives]]<br>from the 69th district|years=2003\u20132006}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mark Meadows (Michigan politician)|Mark Meadows]]}}\n|-\n{{s-par|us-mi-sen}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Virgil Bernero]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[Michigan Senate]]<br>from the 23rd district|years=2006\u20132015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Curtis Hertel Jr.]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mike Prusi]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Minority Leader of the [[Michigan Senate]]|years=2011\u20132015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Jim Ananich]]}}\n|-\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mark Schauer]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee for [[Governor of Michigan]]|years=[[Michigan gubernatorial election, 2018|2018]]}}\n{{s-inc|rows=2|recent}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Stacey Abrams]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Response to the State of the Union address]]|years=[[2020 State of the Union Address|2020]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rick Snyder]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Governor of Michigan]]|years=2019\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before={{Incumbent VPOTUS}}|as=[[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Within Michigan}}\n{{s-aft|after=Mayor of city<br>in which event is held}}\n|-\n{{s-aft|after=Otherwise {{Incumbent U.S. House Speaker}}<br>{{nowrap|''as [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives]]''}}}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Asa Hutchinson]]|as=[[List of Governors of Arkansas|Governor of Arkansas]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Outside Michigan}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ron DeSantis]]|as=[[List of Governors of Florida|Governor of Florida]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Governors of Michigan}}\n{{Current U.S. governors}}\n{{Michigan statewide political officials}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Whitmer, Gretchen}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Michigan House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Michigan Democrats]]\n[[Category:Michigan state senators]]\n[[Category:Michigan State University College of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Lansing, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Women state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Women state legislators in Michigan]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women politicians]]\n", "name_user": "2601:40a:8300:4630:e959:e1bb:e010:3e94", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gretchen_Whitmer"}
{"title_page": "The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!", "text_new": "{{About|the 2012 film|the book on which the film is based|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Billy Hatcher and the Giant Egg: BEWARE! Mario Bros!\n| italic title   = yes\n| image          = PiratesTeaserPoster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = British theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Peter Lord]]<ref name=afi>{{cite web|url=https://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/MovieDetails/68503|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits  (2012)|work=[[AFI Catalog of Feature Films]]|access-date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Julie Lockhart\n* Peter Lord\n* [[David Sproxton]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = [[Gideon Defoe]]<ref name=\"thr\" />\n| based on       = {{based on|''[[The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists]]''|Gideon Defoe}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Hugh Grant]]\n* [[David Tennant]]\n* [[Imelda Staunton]]\n* [[Martin Freeman]]\n* [[Jeremy Piven]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Theodore Shapiro]]<ref>{{cite news | author=filmmusicreporter  | url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2011/03/18/theodore-shapiro-to-score-the-pirates-band-of-misfits/ | title=Theodore Shapiro to Score \u2018The Pirates! Band of Misfits\u2019 | publisher=FilmMusicReporter.com | date=18 March 2011 | accessdate=29 July 2011}}</ref>\n| cinematography = Frank Passingham\n| editing        = Justin Krish\n| studio         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Aardman Animations]]<ref name=afi/>\n* [[Sony Pictures Animation]]<ref name=afi/>\n}}\n| distributor    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]<ref name=afi/>\n* Sony Pictures Animation<ref name=afi/>\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2012|03|28|United Kingdom|2012|04|27|United States|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 78 minutes<ref>{{cite web|title=3D - PIRATES! IN AN ADVENTURE WITH SCIENTISTS|url=http://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/5069|publisher=Cineworld Cinemas|accessdate=1 April 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407144812/http://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/5069|archivedate=7 April 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| country        = United Kingdom<br />United States<ref name=\"BFI\">{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012)|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/50c308c7c7868|publisher=British Film Institute|accessdate=26 December 2016}}</ref>\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $55 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web | url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=pirates12.htm | title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012) | publisher=Box Office Mojo | accessdate=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n| gross          = $123 million<ref name=\"BOM\"/>\n}}\n'''''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!''''' (released in North America, Australia and New Zealand as '''''The Pirates! Band of Misfits''''') is a 2012 British-American<ref name=\"BFI\" /> [[3-D film|3D]] [[stop-motion|stop-motion animated]] [[swashbuckler film|swashbuckler]] [[comedy film]] produced by [[Aardman Animations]] and [[Sony Pictures Animation]] as their second and final collaborative project. Directed by [[Peter Lord]], the film is loosely based on ''[[The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists]]'', the first book from [[Gideon Defoe]]'s ''[[The Pirates!]]'' series.<ref name=\"empire\">{{cite news|last=O'Hara|first=Helen|title=Exclusive! New Pirates! Trailer|url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=32298|accessdate=25 October 2011|newspaper=Empire|date=25 October 2011}}</ref> It follows The Pirate Captain and his crew of amateur pirates in their attempt to win the Pirate of the Year competition.\n\nThe film was distributed by [[Columbia Pictures]] and was released on 28 March 2012 in the United Kingdom, and on 27 April 2012 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pirate Captain and his crew wish you a happy Chinese New Year.|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=306419539404025&set=a.164796320233015.31971.164785560234091&type=1&ref=nf|work=Sony Pictures Animation|publisher=Facebook|accessdate=24 January 2012|date=23 January 2012}}</ref> ''The Pirates!'' features the voices of [[Hugh Grant]], [[Martin Freeman]], [[Imelda Staunton]], [[David Tennant]], [[Jeremy Piven]], [[Salma Hayek]], [[Lenny Henry]] and [[Brian Blessed]]. ''The Pirates!'' is the fifth feature film by [[Aardman Animations]], and its first stop-motion animated feature since ''[[Wallace & Gromit: The Curse of the Were-Rabbit]]'' in 2005, and Aardman's first stop-motion clay animated film released in 3D and shot in 2.35:1 widescreen. The film received positive reviews,<ref name=RT /> while it was a modest box office success, earning $123 million against the budget of $55 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3601&p=.htm | title=2012 Recap (cont.): Losers | publisher=Box Office Mojo | accessdate=4 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe film was nominated for the 2013 [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature]], but lost to [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]]\u00b7[[Pixar]]'s ''[[Brave (2012 film)|Brave]]''.\n\n==Plot==\nIn 1837, the Pirate Captain, inexpert in the ways of pirates, leads a close-knit, rag-tag group of amateur pirates who are trying to make a name for themselves on the high seas. To prove himself and his crew, the Pirate Captain enters the Pirate of the Year competition, the winner being whoever can plunder the most. After several failed attempts to plunder mundane ships, they come across the ''[[HMS Beagle|Beagle]]'' and capture its passenger [[Charles Darwin]]. Darwin recognises the crew's pet \"parrot\", Polly, as the [[Endling|last living]] [[dodo]], and recommends they enter her in the Scientist of the Year competition at the [[Royal Society of London]] for a valuable prize. Secretly, Darwin plans on stealing Polly himself with the help of his trained [[Common chimpanzee|chimpanzee]], Mr. Bobo, as to impress his love interest [[Queen Victoria]].\n\nThe pirates disguise themselves as scientists to enter the competition, and the dodo display wins the top prize, which turns out to be minuscule trinkets and a meeting with the Queen. The Pirate Captain hides Polly before the meeting. There, the Queen requests that the Pirate Captain donate Polly for her petting zoo. The Pirate Captain refuses and accidentally reveals his true identity. The Queen, who hates pirates with a passion, orders him executed, but Darwin steps in to spare the Captain's life, secretly telling the Queen that only the Captain knows where Polly is kept. The Queen pardons the Pirate Captain and orders Darwin to find Polly by any means necessary. Darwin takes the Pirate Captain to a tavern and coaxes out of him that Polly is stashed in his beard. Darwin and Mr. Bobo steal the bird, leading to a chase into the [[Tower of London]] where the Queen is waiting. She dismisses Darwin, and instead offers the Pirate Captain enough money to ensure his win as Pirate of the Year in exchange for Polly. He accepts the offer and returns to his crew, assuring them Polly is still safe in his beard.\n\nAt the Pirate of the Year ceremony, the Pirate Captain wins the grand prize from the Pirate King. But rival pirate Black Bellamy makes the Queen's pardon known to all and explains that if the Pirate Captain has been pardoned, then he is no longer a pirate and, as such, cannot be Pirate of the Year. The Captain is stripped of the prize, treasure, pirate attire, and his pirating licence and is banished from Blood Island by the Pirate King, and admits his loss of Polly to his crew, who abandon him. The Captain returns to London, intent on rescuing Polly. He reunites with Darwin, learning that the Queen is a member of an exclusive society of world leaders that feast on endangered creatures, and that Polly is likely on her flagship, the ''QV1'', to be served at the next meal. The Pirate Captain and Darwin work together to steal an airship to travel to the ''QV1''. Mr. Bobo, meanwhile, goes to find the rest of the Captain's crew to enlist their help.\n\nAboard the ''QV1'', the Queen locates the Pirate Captain and Darwin and attempts to kill both of them, but the Captains Number 2, Mr Bobo and the crew come to their aid and together they best her. In the battle, they accidentally mix the ship's store of [[baking soda]] with [[vinegar]], causing a violent reaction that rends the ship in two after the pirates reconcile. The Pirate Captain rescues Polly and they escape safely, leaving behind a furious Queen. With his reputation among pirates restored because of the large bounty now on his head, the Pirate Captain is reinstated as a Pirate, and he and his crew continue to explore the high seas in search of adventure.\n\nIn a few [[post-credits scene]]s, they leave Darwin on the [[Galapagos Islands]]; Mr. Bobo joins the Pirate Captain's crew; the Queen is left at the mercy of some of the rare animals she had planned on eating; Black Bellamy is stripped of his Pirate of the Year trophy by the Pirate King due to the Pirate Captain's new infamy; and the crew present the Pirate Captain with their very own homemade Pirate of the Year trophy.\n\n==Voice cast==\n[[File:The Pirates Band of Misfits, Hugh Grant, Sydney.jpg|thumb|right|200px|[[Hugh Grant]] in April 2012 at the film's premiere in Sydney, Australia]]\n* [[Hugh Grant]] as Pirate Captain<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2010/12/features/aardman-morphs|title=How Aardman is embracing the digital age|publisher=[[Wired Magazine]]|author=James Silver}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Freeman]] as the Pirate with a Scarf/Number Two<ref name=\"Hitfix1\">{{cite news | last=McWeeny | first=Drew | url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/motion-captured/posts/comic-con-sony-animation-panel | title=Comic-Con: Sony Animation panel puts Aardman's 'Pirates' front and center | publisher=[[HitFix]] | date=22 July 2011 | accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Imelda Staunton]] as [[Queen Victoria]]<ref name=\"empire\" />\n* [[David Tennant]] as [[Charles Darwin]]\n* [[Jeremy Piven]] as Black Bellamy\n* [[Salma Hayek]] as Cutlass Liz<ref name=\"thr\">{{cite web |url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hugh-grant-joins-voice-cast-185746 |title=Hugh Grant Joins Voice Cast for Sony-Backed Pirate Movie|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=5 May 2011 |accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Lenny Henry]] as Peg-Leg Hastings<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=@PeteLordAardman|url=https://www.twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/statuses/136937271982170112|accessdate=17 November 2011|newspaper=Twitter|date=16 November 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Brian Blessed]] as Pirate King<ref name=\"empire\" />\n* [[Russell Tovey]] as Albino Pirate ''(United Kingdom)''<ref>{{cite web | last=Mclean | first=Craig | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/more-mr-nice-guy-why-everyone-loves-russell-tovey-2067802.html | title=More Mr Nice Guy: Why everyone loves Russell Tovey | publisher=[[The Independent]] | date=5 September 2010 | accessdate=4 May 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Anton Yelchin]] as Albino Pirate ''(United States)''<ref>{{cite news|last=Berkshire|first=Geoff|title=Review: 'The Pirates! Band of Misfits' sets sail with Aardman charm|url=http://www.hitfix.com/articles/review-the-pirates-band-of-misfits-sets-sail-with-aardman-charm|accessdate=29 April 2012|newspaper=HitFix|date=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Brendan Gleeson]] as Pirate with Gout<ref name=\"Hitfix1\" />\n* [[Ashley Jensen]] as Surprisingly Curvaceous Pirate<ref name=\"Hitfix1\" />\n* [[Ben Whitehead]] as Pirate Who Likes Sunsets and Kittens ''(United Kingdom)''<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=Captain's Log Production Blog|url=http://thepirates-movie.tumblr.com/post/18982953605/thought-id-just-report-after-back-after-the|accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Nifty Selection of The Pirates! Model Sheets|url=http://www.awn.com/blogs/10till6/nifty-selection-pirates-model-sheets|accessdate=17 August 2012|newspaper=Animation World Network|date=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Al Roker]] as Pirate Who Likes Sunsets and Kittens ''(United States)''\n* [[Mike Cooper (screenwriter)|Mike Cooper]] as Admiral Collingwood\n* [[David Schneider (actor)|David Schneider]] as Scarlett Morgan\n* [[Mitchell Mullen]] as Gameshow Host\n\n==Production==\nAardman extensively used computer graphics to complement and enrich the primarily stop-motion film with visual elements such as sea and scenery.\n\nPeter Lord commented, \"With ''Pirates!,'' I must say that the new technology has made ''Pirates!'' really liberating to make, easy to make because the fact that you can shoot a lot of green screen stuff, the fact that you can easily extend the sets with CG, the fact that you can put the sea in there and a beautiful wooden boat that, frankly, would never sail in a million years, you can take that and put it into a beautiful CG scene and believe it.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Huver|first=Scott|title=EXCL: Lord and Baynham on The Pirates! and Arthur Christmas|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=81049|accessdate=4 September 2011|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|date=15 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Naming===\nFor the release in the United States, the film has been retitled to ''The Pirates! Band of Misfits''. The official explanation from Aardman was that Defoe's books don't have \"the same following outside of the United Kingdom,\" so it was not necessary to keep the original title.<ref name=\"BBCScientistsBand\">{{cite news|last=Cooper|first=Quentin|title=Scientists: Band of misfits?|url=http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20120411-the-scientists-band-of-misfits|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=BBC|date=13 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nHugh Grant, the voice of The Pirate Captain, said that the studio \"didn't think the Americans would like the longer title.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Hardie|first=Giles|title=Cap'n Hugh fires on media|url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/the-diary/capn-hugh-fires-on-media-20120402-1w8wm.html|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=3 April 2012}}</ref> Response from the director of the film, Peter Lord, was that \"some people reckoned the United Kingdom title wouldn't charm/ amuse / work in the United States. Tricky to prove eh?\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Twitter|title=@A7exand3r well, you know, some people reckoned the United Kingdom title wouldn't charm/ amuse / work in the United States. Tricky to prove eh?|url=https://twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/status/272821303684243456|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=Twitter|date=25 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[Quentin Cooper]] of the BBC analysed the change of the title and listed several theories. One of them is that the British audience is more tolerant for the eccentricity of the British animators. Another is that the film makers did not want to challenge the United States viewers who do not accept the theory of evolution. He also developed his own explanation, in which he notes that the word \"scientist\" is rarely used in the Hollywood films due to it not being \"cool,\" representing \"the mad scientist or the dweeby nerd that dress funny, have no social skills, play video games, long for unattainable women.\"<ref name=BBCScientistsBand />\n\n===Controversy===\nIn January 2012, it was reported that the latest trailer of ''The Pirates!'' attracted some very negative reactions from the \"leprosy community\". In the trailer that was released in December, The Pirate Captain lands on a ship demanding gold, but is told by a crew member, \"Gold? Afraid we don't have any gold, old man. This is a leper boat!\". His arm then falls off, to which he responds with \"See?\".<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits - Trailer 2|url=http://trailers.apple.com/trailers/sony_pictures/thepiratesbandofmisfits/|work=iTunes|accessdate=5 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[LEPRA|Lepra Health in Action]] and some officials from the [[World Health Organization]], expressed that the joke shows the illness in a derogatory manner, and it \"reinforces the misconceptions which leads to stigma and discrimination that prevents people from coming forward for treatment.\" They demanded an apology and removal of the offending scene,<ref>{{cite news|last=Lakhani|first=Nina|title=Wallace and Gromit creators in leprosy row|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/wallace-and-gromit-creators-in-leprosy-row-6289472.html|accessdate=5 February 2012|newspaper=The Independent|date=13 January 2012}}</ref> to which Aardman responded: \"After reviewing the matter, we decided to change the scene out of respect and sensitivity for those who suffer from leprosy. The last thing anyone intended was to offend anyone...\".\n\nLHA responded that it was \"genuinely delighted that Aardman has decided to amend the film,\" while the trailer was expected to be pulled down from websites,<ref>{{cite news|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|title=\"The Pirates!\": Aardman To Change Scene After Outcry From Leprosy Orgs|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/01/the-pirates-aardman-to-change-scene-after-outcry-from-leprosy-orgs/|accessdate=5 February 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=24 January 2012}}</ref> and the final version of the film changes the line in question to \"Gold? This is a '''''[[Plague (disease)|plague]]''''' boat, old man! I'd give my right arm for some gold!\", and when his arm falls off, he instead responds with \"Or my left!\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Askew|first=Robin|title=Who wants to be a buccaneer?|url=http://www.venue.co.uk/features/14865-who-wants-to-be-a-buccaneer|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=Venue|date=March 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nThe [[Film score|film's score]] was composed by [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]] who made his animated feature score debut with this film. The score was released digitally by Madison Gate Records on 24 April 2012,<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018The Pirates! Band of Misfits\u2019 Soundtrack Details|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2012/04/19/the-pirates-band-of-misfits-soundtrack-details/|accessdate=26 October 2012|newspaper=Film Music Reporter|date=19 April 2012}}</ref> and as a [[CD-R]] on-demand on 17 May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (Original Motion Picture Score)|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00846O7D8/|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> The film also includes a number of previously released songs by various artists, including \"[[Swords of a Thousand Men]]\" by [[Tenpole Tudor]], \"Ranking Full-Stop\" by [[The Beat (British band)|The Beat]], \"Fiesta\" by [[The Pogues]], \"[[London Calling (song)|London Calling]]\" by [[The Clash]], \"You Can Get It If You Really Want\" by [[Jimmy Cliff]], \"[[Alright (Supergrass song)|Alright]]\" by [[Supergrass]], and \"I'm Not Crying\" by [[Flight of the Conchords]].<ref>The film's credits</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Pirates! Band of Misfits\n| type       = [[Film score]]\n| artist     = [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 24 April 2012\n| recorded   = 2012\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film score|Score]]\n| length     = 51:04\n| label      = Madison Gate Records\n| producer   =\n| chronology = [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]] film scores\n| prev_title = [[The Big Year]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Hope Springs (2012 film)|Hope Springs]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = 51:04\n| headline = Track listing:<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (Original Motion Picture Score)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/pirates!-band-misfits-original/id518744241|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref>\n| title1 = I Hate Pirates!\n| length1 = 2:25\n| title2 = Attacking Ships\n| length2 =2:22\n| title3 = The Competition\n| length3 = 2:18\n| title4 = Not a Total Success\n| length4 = 2:03\n| title5 = The Ascent of Man\n| length5 = 0:38\n| title6 = Masked Monkey Chase\n| length6 = 2:20\n| title7 = Attacking the Beagle\n| length7 = 2:31\n| title8 = Feathery Heart and Soul\n| length8 = 0:43\n| title9 = Fog on the Thames\n| length9 = 1:02\n| title10 = Girl Guides\n| length10 = 2:24\n| title11 = Wait a Mo'!\n| length11 = 5:17\n| title12 = Dreams Turn to Dust\n| length12 = 0:46\n| title13 = The Captain's Dream\n| length13 = 1:33\n| title14 = Baby Clothes\n| length14 = 2:56\n| title15 = The Queen's Lair\n| length15 = 4:28\n| title16 = Market Chase\n| length16 = 1:59\n| title17 = The Dream Fulfilled\n| length17 = 3:23\n| title18 = Panda Face Fritters\n| length18 = 2:51\n| title19 = Poor Defenseless Me\n| length19 = 4:28\n| title20 = Unpardoned\n| length20 = 4:37\n}}\n\n==Release==\n\n===Home media===\n''The Pirates!'' was released on [[DVD]], [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]], and Blu-ray 3D on 28 August 2012 in the United States,<ref>{{cite news|last=Katz|first=Josh|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=8964|accessdate=18 June 2012|newspaper=Blu-ray.com|date=18 June 2012}}</ref> and on 10 September 2012 in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists (DVD)|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B005XZR4U6|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=16 May 2012}}</ref> The film is accompanied with an 18-minute<ref>{{cite web|title=THE PIRATES! BAND OF MISFITS, ADDED VALUE|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/AVV291017/|publisher=British Board of Film Classification|accessdate=6 July 2012}}</ref> short stop motion animated film called ''So You Want to Be a Pirate!'', where The Pirate Captain hosts his own talk show about being a true pirate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sky Movies in the UK posted the first five minutes|url=https://www.facebook.com/SONYPicturesAnimation/posts/356418631061857|accessdate=6 April 2012|date=6 April 2012|author=Sony Pictures Animation|quote=Sky Movies in the UK posted the first five minutes of The Pirates! Band of Misfits short that will plundering on DVD and Blu-ray later this year. Take a look and tell us what you think!}}</ref>\n\nThe short was also released on DVD on 13 August 2012, exclusively at [[Tesco]] stores in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite news|title=Win! A portable DVD player plus So You Want To Be A Pirate! on DVD|url=http://www.goodtoknow.co.uk/money/competitions/60704/win-a-portable-dvd-player-plus-so-you-want-to-be-a-pirate-on-dvd|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=gootoknow}}</ref> As a promotion for the release of ''The Pirates!'', Sony attached to every DVD and Blu-ray a code to download a ''[[LittleBigPlanet 2]]'' minipack of Sackboy clothing that represents 3 of the characters: The Pirate Captain, Cutlass Liz and Black Bellamy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sack it to Me: Arrr! The Pirates Board LittleBigPlanet|url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/2012/08/27/sack-it-to-me-arrr-the-pirates-board-littlebigplanet/|accessdate=29 August 2012|newspaper=PlayStation Blog|date=27 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Minipack|url=http://www.littlebigplanet.com/en/game_guide/ps3/downloadable_content/the_pirates_minipack/|publisher=LittleBigPlanet|accessdate=29 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office===\nThe film has grossed $123,054,041 worldwide. $26 million came from United Kingdom,<ref>{{cite web|title=United Kingdom|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&country=UK&id=pirates12.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=17 July 2012}}</ref> $31 million from the United States and Canada, along with around $92 million from other territories, including the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> As of 2017, it is the fourth [[List of highest-grossing animated films#Stop-motion animation|highest-grossing stop-motion animated film]] of all time.\n\n===Critical response===\nReview aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports that 86% of 150 critics have given the film a positive review; the average rating is 7.24/10. The website's consensus is, \"It may not quite scale Aardman's customary delirious heights, but ''The Pirates!'' still represents some of the smartest, most skillfully animated fare that modern cinema has to offer.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012)|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/pirates_band_of_misfits/|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> Metacritic, which assigns a weighted average score out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, gives the film a score of 73 based on 31 reviews.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-pirates!-band-of-misfits|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+List of awards and nominations\n|[[85th Academy Awards|Academy Awards]]<ref name=\"DeadlineAcademy\">{{cite news|last=Finke|first=Nikki|title=OSCARS: 85th Academy Award Nominations \u2013 Only 9 Best Pictures; \u2018Lincoln\u2019 Leads With 12 Nods, \u2018Life Of Pi\u2019 11, \u2018Les Mis\u00e9rables\u2019 And \u2018Silver Linings Playbook\u2019 8, \u2018Argo\u2019 7, \u2018Skyfall\u2019 And \u2018Amour\u2019 And \u2018Zero Dark Thirty\u2019 And \u2018Django Unchained\u2019 5|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/01/oscar-nominations-2013-list-announced-85th-academy-awards-nominees/|accessdate=10 January 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=10 January 2013}}</ref>\n|[[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]]\n|[[Peter Lord]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[Annie Award]]s<ref>{{cite news|title=Annie Award Nominations Unveiled|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/12/2012-annie-award-nominations/|accessdate=3 December 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=3 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Beck|first=Jerry|title=Annie Award Winners|url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/events/annie-award-winners-77380.html|accessdate=3 February 2013|newspaper=[[Cartoon Brew]]|date=2 February 2013}}</ref>\n|Best Animated Feature\n|Julie Lockhart, Peter Lord and [[David Sproxton]]\n|rowspan=5 {{nom}}\n|-\n|Character Animation in a Feature Production\n|Will Becher\n|-\n|Production Design in an Animated Feature Production\n|Norman Garwood, Matt Berry\n|-\n|Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production\n|[[Imelda Staunton]] as Queen Victoria\n|-\n|Writing in an Animated Feature Production\n|Gideon Defoe\n|-\n|[[25th European Film Awards|European Film Awards]]<ref name=\"cartoon\">{{cite news |url=http://blog.bcdb.com/pirates-sets-sail-european-film-awards-4675/ |title=Pirates Sets Sail For European Film Awards|first=Paul|last=Anderson |publisher=Big Cartoon News |date=17 September 2012|accessdate=17 September 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The 25th European Film Awards: Winners|url=http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/News-detail.155.0.html?&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=88&cHash=b859c57aafcfa00d80f829301a1e03ec|accessdate=4 December 2012|newspaper=European Film Academy|date=1 December 2012}}</ref>\n|Best Animated Feature Film\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Visual Effects Society Awards 2012|Visual Effects Society]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Nominations for the 11th Annual VES Awards|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/gamenews.php?id=98578|accessdate=7 January 2013|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|date=7 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=VES Awards: \u2018Life Of Pi\u2019 Wins 4 Including Feature, \u2018Brave\u2019, \u2018Game Of Thrones\u2019 Other Big Winners|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/02/visual-effects-society-awards-2013-winners-list/|accessdate=7 February 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=5 February 2013}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Animated Character in an Animated Feature Motion Picture\n| Will Becher, Jay Grace, Loyd Price\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Possible sequel==\nBy August 2011, Aardman had been already working on a sequel idea,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=Happy to say we're working on a sequel idea already. Just so we're prepared!|url=https://www.twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/status/102779771037028352|work=Twitter|date=14 August 2011|accessdate=15 August 2011}}</ref> and by June 2012, a story had been prepared, awaiting Sony to back the project.<ref>{{cite news|last=Jardine|first=William|title=Interview: Peter Lord, Co-founder of Aardman and Director of The Pirates!|url=http://www.a113animation.com/2012/06/interview-peter-lord-co-founder-of.html|accessdate=6 July 2012|newspaper=A113 Animation|date=21 June 2012}}</ref> Eventually, Sony decided not to support the project due to insufficient international earnings. According to Lord, \"it got close, but not quite close enough. I was all fired up for doing more. It was such fun to do! We actually have a poster for ''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Cowboys!''. That would have been just great.\"<ref name=\"THRCoFoundersQ&A\">{{cite news|last1=Ritman|first1=Alex|title=Aardman Animations Co-Founders Talk 'Early Man,' 'Shaun the Sheep' and Their Swashbuckling Near-Miss (Q&A)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/afm-2016-aardman-animations-founders-shaun-sheep-success-brexit-consequences-943498|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n{{wikiquote|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists (film)}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.sonypictures.com/movies/thepiratesbandofmisfits|''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!''}} \u2013 official site (US)\n*{{IMDb title|1430626|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{bcdb title|132592|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{allrovi movie|538915|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{mojo title|pirates12|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{rotten-tomatoes|pirates_band_of_misfits|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{metacritic film|the-pirates!-band-of-misfits|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{bcdb title|145629|So You Want to Be a Pirate!}}\n\n{{The Pirates}}\n{{Aardman Animations}}\n{{Sony Pictures Animation}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pirates In An Adventure With Scientists}}\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:2012 3D films]]\n[[Category:2012 animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s action comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:Aardman Animations films]]\n[[Category:American action adventure films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American action comedy films]]\n[[Category:American adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy adventure films]]\n[[Category:Animated action films]]\n[[Category:Animated adventure films]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:British 3D films]]\n[[Category:British adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:British animated films]]\n[[Category:British children's adventure films]]\n[[Category:British children's animated films]]\n[[Category:British children's comedy films]]\n[[Category:British children's fantasy films]]\n[[Category:British fantasy adventure films]]\n[[Category:British historical films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:Clay animation films]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Charles Darwin]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Queen Victoria on film]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1837]]\n[[Category:Films set in London]]\n[[Category:Pirate films]]\n[[Category:Swashbuckler films]]\n[[Category:2010s stop-motion animated films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures animated films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Sony Pictures Animation films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Peter Lord]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Theodore Shapiro]]\n[[Category:3D animated films]]\n[[Category:2012 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the 2012 film|the book on which the film is based|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!\n| italic title   = yes\n| image          = PiratesTeaserPoster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = British theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Peter Lord]]<ref name=afi>{{cite web|url=https://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/MovieDetails/68503|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits  (2012)|work=[[AFI Catalog of Feature Films]]|access-date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Julie Lockhart\n* Peter Lord\n* [[David Sproxton]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = [[Gideon Defoe]]<ref name=\"thr\" />\n| based on       = {{based on|''[[The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists]]''|Gideon Defoe}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Hugh Grant]]\n* [[David Tennant]]\n* [[Imelda Staunton]]\n* [[Martin Freeman]]\n* [[Jeremy Piven]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Theodore Shapiro]]<ref>{{cite news | author=filmmusicreporter  | url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2011/03/18/theodore-shapiro-to-score-the-pirates-band-of-misfits/ | title=Theodore Shapiro to Score \u2018The Pirates! Band of Misfits\u2019 | publisher=FilmMusicReporter.com | date=18 March 2011 | accessdate=29 July 2011}}</ref>\n| cinematography = Frank Passingham\n| editing        = Justin Krish\n| studio         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Aardman Animations]]<ref name=afi/>\n* [[Sony Pictures Animation]]<ref name=afi/>\n}}\n| distributor    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]<ref name=afi/>\n* Sony Pictures Animation<ref name=afi/>\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2012|03|28|United Kingdom|2012|04|27|United States|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 88 minutes<ref>{{cite web|title=3D - PIRATES! IN AN ADVENTURE WITH SCIENTISTS|url=http://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/5069|publisher=Cineworld Cinemas|accessdate=1 April 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407144812/http://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/5069|archivedate=7 April 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| country        = United Kingdom<br />United States<ref name=\"BFI\">{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012)|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/50c308c7c7868|publisher=British Film Institute|accessdate=26 December 2016}}</ref>\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $55 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web | url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=pirates12.htm | title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012) | publisher=Box Office Mojo | accessdate=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n| gross          = $123 million<ref name=\"BOM\"/>\n}}\n'''''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!''''' (released in North America, Australia and New Zealand as '''''The Pirates! Band of Misfits''''') is a 2012 British-American<ref name=\"BFI\" /> [[3-D film|3D]] [[stop-motion|stop-motion animated]] [[swashbuckler film|swashbuckler]] [[comedy film]] produced by [[Aardman Animations]] and [[Sony Pictures Animation]] as their second and final collaborative project. Directed by [[Peter Lord]], the film is loosely based on ''[[The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists]]'', the first book from [[Gideon Defoe]]'s ''[[The Pirates!]]'' series.<ref name=\"empire\">{{cite news|last=O'Hara|first=Helen|title=Exclusive! New Pirates! Trailer|url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=32298|accessdate=25 October 2011|newspaper=Empire|date=25 October 2011}}</ref> It follows The Pirate Captain and his crew of amateur pirates in their attempt to win the Pirate of the Year competition.\n\nThe film was distributed by [[Columbia Pictures]] and was released on 28 March 2012 in the United Kingdom, and on 27 April 2012 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pirate Captain and his crew wish you a happy Chinese New Year.|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=306419539404025&set=a.164796320233015.31971.164785560234091&type=1&ref=nf|work=Sony Pictures Animation|publisher=Facebook|accessdate=24 January 2012|date=23 January 2012}}</ref> ''The Pirates!'' features the voices of [[Hugh Grant]], [[Martin Freeman]], [[Imelda Staunton]], [[David Tennant]], [[Jeremy Piven]], [[Salma Hayek]], [[Lenny Henry]] and [[Brian Blessed]]. ''The Pirates!'' is the fifth feature film by [[Aardman Animations]], and its first stop-motion animated feature since ''[[Wallace & Gromit: The Curse of the Were-Rabbit]]'' in 2005, and Aardman's first stop-motion clay animated film released in 3D and shot in 2.35:1 widescreen. The film received positive reviews,<ref name=RT /> while it was a modest box office success, earning $123 million against the budget of $55 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3601&p=.htm | title=2012 Recap (cont.): Losers | publisher=Box Office Mojo | accessdate=4 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe film was nominated for the 2013 [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature]], but lost to [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]]\u00b7[[Pixar]]'s ''[[Brave (2012 film)|Brave]]''.\n\n==Plot==\nIn 1837, the Pirate Captain, inexpert in the ways of pirates, leads a close-knit, rag-tag group of amateur pirates who are trying to make a name for themselves on the high seas. To prove himself and his crew, the Pirate Captain enters the Pirate of the Year competition, the winner being whoever can plunder the most. After several failed attempts to plunder mundane ships, they come across the ''[[HMS Beagle|Beagle]]'' and capture its passenger [[Charles Darwin]]. Darwin recognises the crew's pet \"parrot\", Polly, as the [[Endling|last living]] [[dodo]], and recommends they enter her in the Scientist of the Year competition at the [[Royal Society of London]] for a valuable prize. Secretly, Darwin plans on stealing Polly himself with the help of his trained [[Common chimpanzee|chimpanzee]], Mr. Bobo, as to impress his love interest [[Queen Victoria]].\n\nThe pirates disguise themselves as scientists to enter the competition, and the dodo display wins the top prize, which turns out to be minuscule trinkets and a meeting with the Queen. The Pirate Captain hides Polly before the meeting. There, the Queen requests that the Pirate Captain donate Polly for her petting zoo. The Pirate Captain refuses and accidentally reveals his true identity. The Queen, who hates pirates with a passion, orders him executed, but Darwin steps in to spare the Captain's life, secretly telling the Queen that only the Captain knows where Polly is kept. The Queen pardons the Pirate Captain and orders Darwin to find Polly by any means necessary. Darwin takes the Pirate Captain to a tavern and coaxes out of him that Polly is stashed in his beard. Darwin and Mr. Bobo steal the bird, leading to a chase into the [[Tower of London]] where the Queen is waiting. She dismisses Darwin, and instead offers the Pirate Captain enough money to ensure his win as Pirate of the Year in exchange for Polly. He accepts the offer and returns to his crew, assuring them Polly is still safe in his beard.\n\nAt the Pirate of the Year ceremony, the Pirate Captain wins the grand prize from the Pirate King. But rival pirate Black Bellamy makes the Queen's pardon known to all and explains that if the Pirate Captain has been pardoned, then he is no longer a pirate and, as such, cannot be Pirate of the Year. The Captain is stripped of the prize, treasure, pirate attire, and his pirating licence and is banished from Blood Island by the Pirate King, and admits his loss of Polly to his crew, who abandon him. The Captain returns to London, intent on rescuing Polly. He reunites with Darwin, learning that the Queen is a member of an exclusive society of world leaders that feast on endangered creatures, and that Polly is likely on her flagship, the ''QV1'', to be served at the next meal. The Pirate Captain and Darwin work together to steal an airship to travel to the ''QV1''. Mr. Bobo, meanwhile, goes to find the rest of the Captain's crew to enlist their help.\n\nAboard the ''QV1'', the Queen locates the Pirate Captain and Darwin and attempts to kill both of them, but the Captains Number 2, Mr Bobo and the crew come to their aid and together they best her. In the battle, they accidentally mix the ship's store of [[baking soda]] with [[vinegar]], causing a violent reaction that rends the ship in two after the pirates reconcile. The Pirate Captain rescues Polly and they escape safely, leaving behind a furious Queen. With his reputation among pirates restored because of the large bounty now on his head, the Pirate Captain is reinstated as a Pirate, and he and his crew continue to explore the high seas in search of adventure.\n\nIn a few [[post-credits scene]]s, they leave Darwin on the [[Galapagos Islands]]; Mr. Bobo joins the Pirate Captain's crew; the Queen is left at the mercy of some of the rare animals she had planned on eating; Black Bellamy is stripped of his Pirate of the Year trophy by the Pirate King due to the Pirate Captain's new infamy; and the crew present the Pirate Captain with their very own homemade Pirate of the Year trophy.\n\n==Voice cast==\n[[File:The Pirates Band of Misfits, Hugh Grant, Sydney.jpg|thumb|right|200px|[[Hugh Grant]] in April 2012 at the film's premiere in Sydney, Australia]]\n* [[Hugh Grant]] as Pirate Captain<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2010/12/features/aardman-morphs|title=How Aardman is embracing the digital age|publisher=[[Wired Magazine]]|author=James Silver}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Freeman]] as the Pirate with a Scarf/Number Two<ref name=\"Hitfix1\">{{cite news | last=McWeeny | first=Drew | url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/motion-captured/posts/comic-con-sony-animation-panel | title=Comic-Con: Sony Animation panel puts Aardman's 'Pirates' front and center | publisher=[[HitFix]] | date=22 July 2011 | accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Imelda Staunton]] as [[Queen Victoria]]<ref name=\"empire\" />\n* [[David Tennant]] as [[Charles Darwin]]\n* [[Jeremy Piven]] as Black Bellamy\n* [[Salma Hayek]] as Cutlass Liz<ref name=\"thr\">{{cite web |url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hugh-grant-joins-voice-cast-185746 |title=Hugh Grant Joins Voice Cast for Sony-Backed Pirate Movie|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=5 May 2011 |accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Lenny Henry]] as Peg-Leg Hastings<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=@PeteLordAardman|url=https://www.twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/statuses/136937271982170112|accessdate=17 November 2011|newspaper=Twitter|date=16 November 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Brian Blessed]] as Pirate King<ref name=\"empire\" />\n* [[Russell Tovey]] as Albino Pirate ''(United Kingdom)''<ref>{{cite web | last=Mclean | first=Craig | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/more-mr-nice-guy-why-everyone-loves-russell-tovey-2067802.html | title=More Mr Nice Guy: Why everyone loves Russell Tovey | publisher=[[The Independent]] | date=5 September 2010 | accessdate=4 May 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Anton Yelchin]] as Albino Pirate ''(United States)''<ref>{{cite news|last=Berkshire|first=Geoff|title=Review: 'The Pirates! Band of Misfits' sets sail with Aardman charm|url=http://www.hitfix.com/articles/review-the-pirates-band-of-misfits-sets-sail-with-aardman-charm|accessdate=29 April 2012|newspaper=HitFix|date=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Brendan Gleeson]] as Pirate with Gout<ref name=\"Hitfix1\" />\n* [[Ashley Jensen]] as Surprisingly Curvaceous Pirate<ref name=\"Hitfix1\" />\n* [[Ben Whitehead]] as Pirate Who Likes Sunsets and Kittens ''(United Kingdom)''<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=Captain's Log Production Blog|url=http://thepirates-movie.tumblr.com/post/18982953605/thought-id-just-report-after-back-after-the|accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Nifty Selection of The Pirates! Model Sheets|url=http://www.awn.com/blogs/10till6/nifty-selection-pirates-model-sheets|accessdate=17 August 2012|newspaper=Animation World Network|date=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Al Roker]] as Pirate Who Likes Sunsets and Kittens ''(United States)''\n* [[Mike Cooper (screenwriter)|Mike Cooper]] as Admiral Collingwood\n* [[David Schneider (actor)|David Schneider]] as Scarlett Morgan\n* [[Mitchell Mullen]] as Gameshow Host\n\n==Production==\nAardman extensively used computer graphics to complement and enrich the primarily stop-motion film with visual elements such as sea and scenery.\n\nPeter Lord commented, \"With ''Pirates!,'' I must say that the new technology has made ''Pirates!'' really liberating to make, easy to make because the fact that you can shoot a lot of green screen stuff, the fact that you can easily extend the sets with CG, the fact that you can put the sea in there and a beautiful wooden boat that, frankly, would never sail in a million years, you can take that and put it into a beautiful CG scene and believe it.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Huver|first=Scott|title=EXCL: Lord and Baynham on The Pirates! and Arthur Christmas|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=81049|accessdate=4 September 2011|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|date=15 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Naming===\nFor the release in the United States, the film has been retitled to ''The Pirates! Band of Misfits''. The official explanation from Aardman was that Defoe's books don't have \"the same following outside of the United Kingdom,\" so it was not necessary to keep the original title.<ref name=\"BBCScientistsBand\">{{cite news|last=Cooper|first=Quentin|title=Scientists: Band of misfits?|url=http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20120411-the-scientists-band-of-misfits|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=BBC|date=13 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nHugh Grant, the voice of The Pirate Captain, said that the studio \"didn't think the Americans would like the longer title.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Hardie|first=Giles|title=Cap'n Hugh fires on media|url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/the-diary/capn-hugh-fires-on-media-20120402-1w8wm.html|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=3 April 2012}}</ref> Response from the director of the film, Peter Lord, was that \"some people reckoned the United Kingdom title wouldn't charm/ amuse / work in the United States. Tricky to prove eh?\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Lord|first=Twitter|title=@A7exand3r well, you know, some people reckoned the United Kingdom title wouldn't charm/ amuse / work in the United States. Tricky to prove eh?|url=https://twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/status/272821303684243456|accessdate=30 November 2012|newspaper=Twitter|date=25 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[Quentin Cooper]] of the BBC analysed the change of the title and listed several theories. One of them is that the British audience is more tolerant for the eccentricity of the British animators. Another is that the film makers did not want to challenge the United States viewers who do not accept the theory of evolution. He also developed his own explanation, in which he notes that the word \"scientist\" is rarely used in the Hollywood films due to it not being \"cool,\" representing \"the mad scientist or the dweeby nerd that dress funny, have no social skills, play video games, long for unattainable women.\"<ref name=BBCScientistsBand />\n\n===Controversy===\nIn January 2012, it was reported that the latest trailer of ''The Pirates!'' attracted some very negative reactions from the \"leprosy community\". In the trailer that was released in December, The Pirate Captain lands on a ship demanding gold, but is told by a crew member, \"Gold? Afraid we don't have any gold, old man. This is a leper boat!\". His arm then falls off, to which he responds with \"See?\".<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits - Trailer 2|url=http://trailers.apple.com/trailers/sony_pictures/thepiratesbandofmisfits/|work=iTunes|accessdate=5 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[LEPRA|Lepra Health in Action]] and some officials from the [[World Health Organization]], expressed that the joke shows the illness in a derogatory manner, and it \"reinforces the misconceptions which leads to stigma and discrimination that prevents people from coming forward for treatment.\" They demanded an apology and removal of the offending scene,<ref>{{cite news|last=Lakhani|first=Nina|title=Wallace and Gromit creators in leprosy row|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/wallace-and-gromit-creators-in-leprosy-row-6289472.html|accessdate=5 February 2012|newspaper=The Independent|date=13 January 2012}}</ref> to which Aardman responded: \"After reviewing the matter, we decided to change the scene out of respect and sensitivity for those who suffer from leprosy. The last thing anyone intended was to offend anyone...\".\n\nLHA responded that it was \"genuinely delighted that Aardman has decided to amend the film,\" while the trailer was expected to be pulled down from websites,<ref>{{cite news|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|title=\"The Pirates!\": Aardman To Change Scene After Outcry From Leprosy Orgs|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/01/the-pirates-aardman-to-change-scene-after-outcry-from-leprosy-orgs/|accessdate=5 February 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=24 January 2012}}</ref> and the final version of the film changes the line in question to \"Gold? This is a '''''[[Plague (disease)|plague]]''''' boat, old man! I'd give my right arm for some gold!\", and when his arm falls off, he instead responds with \"Or my left!\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Askew|first=Robin|title=Who wants to be a buccaneer?|url=http://www.venue.co.uk/features/14865-who-wants-to-be-a-buccaneer|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=Venue|date=March 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nThe [[Film score|film's score]] was composed by [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]] who made his animated feature score debut with this film. The score was released digitally by Madison Gate Records on 24 April 2012,<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018The Pirates! Band of Misfits\u2019 Soundtrack Details|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2012/04/19/the-pirates-band-of-misfits-soundtrack-details/|accessdate=26 October 2012|newspaper=Film Music Reporter|date=19 April 2012}}</ref> and as a [[CD-R]] on-demand on 17 May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (Original Motion Picture Score)|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00846O7D8/|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> The film also includes a number of previously released songs by various artists, including \"[[Swords of a Thousand Men]]\" by [[Tenpole Tudor]], \"Ranking Full-Stop\" by [[The Beat (British band)|The Beat]], \"Fiesta\" by [[The Pogues]], \"[[London Calling (song)|London Calling]]\" by [[The Clash]], \"You Can Get It If You Really Want\" by [[Jimmy Cliff]], \"[[Alright (Supergrass song)|Alright]]\" by [[Supergrass]], and \"I'm Not Crying\" by [[Flight of the Conchords]].<ref>The film's credits</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Pirates! Band of Misfits\n| type       = [[Film score]]\n| artist     = [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 24 April 2012\n| recorded   = 2012\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film score|Score]]\n| length     = 51:04\n| label      = Madison Gate Records\n| producer   =\n| chronology = [[Theodore Shapiro (composer)|Theodore Shapiro]] film scores\n| prev_title = [[The Big Year]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Hope Springs (2012 film)|Hope Springs]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = 51:04\n| headline = Track listing:<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (Original Motion Picture Score)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/pirates!-band-misfits-original/id518744241|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref>\n| title1 = I Hate Pirates!\n| length1 = 2:25\n| title2 = Attacking Ships\n| length2 =2:22\n| title3 = The Competition\n| length3 = 2:18\n| title4 = Not a Total Success\n| length4 = 2:03\n| title5 = The Ascent of Man\n| length5 = 0:38\n| title6 = Masked Monkey Chase\n| length6 = 2:20\n| title7 = Attacking the Beagle\n| length7 = 2:31\n| title8 = Feathery Heart and Soul\n| length8 = 0:43\n| title9 = Fog on the Thames\n| length9 = 1:02\n| title10 = Girl Guides\n| length10 = 2:24\n| title11 = Wait a Mo'!\n| length11 = 5:17\n| title12 = Dreams Turn to Dust\n| length12 = 0:46\n| title13 = The Captain's Dream\n| length13 = 1:33\n| title14 = Baby Clothes\n| length14 = 2:56\n| title15 = The Queen's Lair\n| length15 = 4:28\n| title16 = Market Chase\n| length16 = 1:59\n| title17 = The Dream Fulfilled\n| length17 = 3:23\n| title18 = Panda Face Fritters\n| length18 = 2:51\n| title19 = Poor Defenseless Me\n| length19 = 4:28\n| title20 = Unpardoned\n| length20 = 4:37\n}}\n\n==Release==\n\n===Home media===\n''The Pirates!'' was released on [[DVD]], [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]], and Blu-ray 3D on 28 August 2012 in the United States,<ref>{{cite news|last=Katz|first=Josh|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=8964|accessdate=18 June 2012|newspaper=Blu-ray.com|date=18 June 2012}}</ref> and on 10 September 2012 in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists (DVD)|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B005XZR4U6|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=16 May 2012}}</ref> The film is accompanied with an 18-minute<ref>{{cite web|title=THE PIRATES! BAND OF MISFITS, ADDED VALUE|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/AVV291017/|publisher=British Board of Film Classification|accessdate=6 July 2012}}</ref> short stop motion animated film called ''So You Want to Be a Pirate!'', where The Pirate Captain hosts his own talk show about being a true pirate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sky Movies in the UK posted the first five minutes|url=https://www.facebook.com/SONYPicturesAnimation/posts/356418631061857|accessdate=6 April 2012|date=6 April 2012|author=Sony Pictures Animation|quote=Sky Movies in the UK posted the first five minutes of The Pirates! Band of Misfits short that will plundering on DVD and Blu-ray later this year. Take a look and tell us what you think!}}</ref>\n\nThe short was also released on DVD on 13 August 2012, exclusively at [[Tesco]] stores in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite news|title=Win! A portable DVD player plus So You Want To Be A Pirate! on DVD|url=http://www.goodtoknow.co.uk/money/competitions/60704/win-a-portable-dvd-player-plus-so-you-want-to-be-a-pirate-on-dvd|accessdate=22 August 2012|newspaper=gootoknow}}</ref> As a promotion for the release of ''The Pirates!'', Sony attached to every DVD and Blu-ray a code to download a ''[[LittleBigPlanet 2]]'' minipack of Sackboy clothing that represents 3 of the characters: The Pirate Captain, Cutlass Liz and Black Bellamy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sack it to Me: Arrr! The Pirates Board LittleBigPlanet|url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/2012/08/27/sack-it-to-me-arrr-the-pirates-board-littlebigplanet/|accessdate=29 August 2012|newspaper=PlayStation Blog|date=27 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Minipack|url=http://www.littlebigplanet.com/en/game_guide/ps3/downloadable_content/the_pirates_minipack/|publisher=LittleBigPlanet|accessdate=29 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office===\nThe film has grossed $123,054,041 worldwide. $26 million came from United Kingdom,<ref>{{cite web|title=United Kingdom|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&country=UK&id=pirates12.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=17 July 2012}}</ref> $31 million from the United States and Canada, along with around $92 million from other territories, including the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> As of 2017, it is the fourth [[List of highest-grossing animated films#Stop-motion animation|highest-grossing stop-motion animated film]] of all time.\n\n===Critical response===\nReview aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports that 86% of 150 critics have given the film a positive review; the average rating is 7.24/10. The website's consensus is, \"It may not quite scale Aardman's customary delirious heights, but ''The Pirates!'' still represents some of the smartest, most skillfully animated fare that modern cinema has to offer.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits (2012)|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/pirates_band_of_misfits/|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> Metacritic, which assigns a weighted average score out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, gives the film a score of 73 based on 31 reviews.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Pirates! Band of Misfits|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-pirates!-band-of-misfits|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+List of awards and nominations\n|[[85th Academy Awards|Academy Awards]]<ref name=\"DeadlineAcademy\">{{cite news|last=Finke|first=Nikki|title=OSCARS: 85th Academy Award Nominations \u2013 Only 9 Best Pictures; \u2018Lincoln\u2019 Leads With 12 Nods, \u2018Life Of Pi\u2019 11, \u2018Les Mis\u00e9rables\u2019 And \u2018Silver Linings Playbook\u2019 8, \u2018Argo\u2019 7, \u2018Skyfall\u2019 And \u2018Amour\u2019 And \u2018Zero Dark Thirty\u2019 And \u2018Django Unchained\u2019 5|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/01/oscar-nominations-2013-list-announced-85th-academy-awards-nominees/|accessdate=10 January 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=10 January 2013}}</ref>\n|[[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]]\n|[[Peter Lord]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[Annie Award]]s<ref>{{cite news|title=Annie Award Nominations Unveiled|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/12/2012-annie-award-nominations/|accessdate=3 December 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=3 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Beck|first=Jerry|title=Annie Award Winners|url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/events/annie-award-winners-77380.html|accessdate=3 February 2013|newspaper=[[Cartoon Brew]]|date=2 February 2013}}</ref>\n|Best Animated Feature\n|Julie Lockhart, Peter Lord and [[David Sproxton]]\n|rowspan=5 {{nom}}\n|-\n|Character Animation in a Feature Production\n|Will Becher\n|-\n|Production Design in an Animated Feature Production\n|Norman Garwood, Matt Berry\n|-\n|Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production\n|[[Imelda Staunton]] as Queen Victoria\n|-\n|Writing in an Animated Feature Production\n|Gideon Defoe\n|-\n|[[25th European Film Awards|European Film Awards]]<ref name=\"cartoon\">{{cite news |url=http://blog.bcdb.com/pirates-sets-sail-european-film-awards-4675/ |title=Pirates Sets Sail For European Film Awards|first=Paul|last=Anderson |publisher=Big Cartoon News |date=17 September 2012|accessdate=17 September 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The 25th European Film Awards: Winners|url=http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/News-detail.155.0.html?&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=88&cHash=b859c57aafcfa00d80f829301a1e03ec|accessdate=4 December 2012|newspaper=European Film Academy|date=1 December 2012}}</ref>\n|Best Animated Feature Film\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Visual Effects Society Awards 2012|Visual Effects Society]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Nominations for the 11th Annual VES Awards|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/gamenews.php?id=98578|accessdate=7 January 2013|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|date=7 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=VES Awards: \u2018Life Of Pi\u2019 Wins 4 Including Feature, \u2018Brave\u2019, \u2018Game Of Thrones\u2019 Other Big Winners|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/02/visual-effects-society-awards-2013-winners-list/|accessdate=7 February 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=5 February 2013}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Animated Character in an Animated Feature Motion Picture\n| Will Becher, Jay Grace, Loyd Price\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Possible sequel==\nBy August 2011, Aardman had been already working on a sequel idea,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lord|first=Peter|title=Happy to say we're working on a sequel idea already. Just so we're prepared!|url=https://www.twitter.com/PeteLordAardman/status/102779771037028352|work=Twitter|date=14 August 2011|accessdate=15 August 2011}}</ref> and by June 2012, a story had been prepared, awaiting Sony to back the project.<ref>{{cite news|last=Jardine|first=William|title=Interview: Peter Lord, Co-founder of Aardman and Director of The Pirates!|url=http://www.a113animation.com/2012/06/interview-peter-lord-co-founder-of.html|accessdate=6 July 2012|newspaper=A113 Animation|date=21 June 2012}}</ref> Eventually, Sony decided not to support the project due to insufficient international earnings. According to Lord, \"it got close, but not quite close enough. I was all fired up for doing more. It was such fun to do! We actually have a poster for ''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Cowboys!''. That would have been just great.\"<ref name=\"THRCoFoundersQ&A\">{{cite news|last1=Ritman|first1=Alex|title=Aardman Animations Co-Founders Talk 'Early Man,' 'Shaun the Sheep' and Their Swashbuckling Near-Miss (Q&A)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/afm-2016-aardman-animations-founders-shaun-sheep-success-brexit-consequences-943498|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n{{wikiquote|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists (film)}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.sonypictures.com/movies/thepiratesbandofmisfits|''The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!''}} \u2013 official site (US)\n*{{IMDb title|1430626|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{bcdb title|132592|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{allrovi movie|538915|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{mojo title|pirates12|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{rotten-tomatoes|pirates_band_of_misfits|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{metacritic film|the-pirates!-band-of-misfits|The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!}}\n*{{bcdb title|145629|So You Want to Be a Pirate!}}\n\n{{The Pirates}}\n{{Aardman Animations}}\n{{Sony Pictures Animation}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pirates I