Tahara]]\n| Decision (unanimous)\n| [[2007_in_Shooto#Shooto:_Shooting_Disco_3:_Everybody_Fight_Now|Shooto: Shooting Disco 3: Everybody Fight Now]]\n| {{dts|2007|October|20}}\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 5:00\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 1-0\n| Takahisa Toyoshima\n| TKO (punches)\n| [[2007_in_Shooto#Shooto:_Back_To_Our_Roots_4|Shooto: Back To Our Roots 4]]\n| {{dts|2007|July|15}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:53\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n{{end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Sherdog}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ito, Junji}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Japanese male mixed martial artists]]\n[[Category:Strawweight mixed martial artists]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese mixed martial artist}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Junji Ito \n| native_name     = \u4f0a\u85e4 \u6df3\u4e8c\n| other_names     = Junji Sarumaru<br>(\u733f\u4e38\u30b8\u30e5\u30f3\u30b8) \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1986|8|23}}\n| birth_place     = [[Yokohama]], [[Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa]], [[Japan]]\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       =\n| nationality     =  [[Japanese people|Japanese]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=4}}<ref>{{cite web |title=\u733f\u4e38 \u30b8\u30e5\u30f3\u30b8 |url=http://www.shooto-mma.com/fighters/?id=29 |website=Shooto-mma |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n| weight          = {{convert|114|lb|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Strawweight (MMA)|Strawweight]]\n| reach           = \n| style           = \n| stance          = orthodox\n| fighting_out_of = \n| team            = Shooting Gym Yokohama<ref>{{cite web |title=\u4fee\u6597GYM\u6771\u4eac / 8 \u9078\u624b |url=http://www.shooto-mma.com/fighters/?pg=fighters&gymid=117 |website=Shooto-mma |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rank            =\n| years_active    =\n| mma_kowin       = 9\n| mma_subwin      = 1\n| mma_decwin      = 6\n| mma_koloss      = 2\n| mma_subloss     = 3\n| mma_decloss     = 3\n| mma_draw        = 2\n| mma_nc          = \n| url             =\n| sherdog         = 23226\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Junji Ito'''|\u4f0a\u85e4\u6df3\u4e8c|It\u014d Junji|extra=born August 23, 1986}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] who competes in the [[Strawweight (MMA)|strawweight]] division of [[Shooto]], where he is the #1 ranked contender<ref>{{cite web |title=2020\u5e7403\u6708\u5ea6 \u4e16\u754c\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 |url=http://www.shooto-mma.com/ranking/ |website=Shooto-mma |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>. He is a former four time Shooto title challenger, fighiting for the Shooto Strawweight Championship once and thrice for the Shooto Flyweight Championship.\n\n'''\"Junji Sarumaru\"''' (\u733f\u4e38\u30b8\u30e5\u30f3\u30b8) is ring name of Ito in Japan.\n\n==Mixed martial arts career==\nJunji Ito has spent his entire career fighting for the [[Shooto]] organization. He is known for his punching power,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Shooto-Rookie-Kings-Crowned-Sarumaru-Steals-the-Show-28871|title=Shooto Rookie Kings Crowned; \u2018Sarumaru\u2019 Steals the Show|publisher=Sherdog.com|date=2010-12-08}}</ref> with the majority of his wins coming by knockout. \n\nJunji Ito began his MMA career 2007, with Shooto, where he amassed an 7-2 record in three years of competing. His first serious challenge came against Junji Ikoma when he fought for the [[Shooto]] flyweight title. He lost a unanimous decision. During Shooto: Bout Sustain 3, he faced Yuki Shojo, winning the bout by majority decision.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yuki Shojo vs. Junji Ito |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/48993-shooto-3rd-round-junji-sarumaru-ito-vs-yuki-shojo |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> This win earned him a title shot against the strawweight champion [[Mikihito Yamagami]]. He would lose the fight in the second round, by way of a rear naked choke.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mikihito Yamagami vs. Junji Ito |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/65433-shooto-10th-round-mikihito-yamagami-vs-junji-sarumaru-ito |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Ito bounced back with a decision win against Tadaaki Yamamoto,<ref>{{cite web |title=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/106540-shooto-gig-tokyo-vol-15-junji-sarumaru-ito-vs-tadaaki-oniboz-yamamoto |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/65433-shooto-10th-round-mikihito-yamagami-vs-junji-sarumaru-ito |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> and fought against [[Shinya Murofushi]] for the vacant flyweight title. He would against fail to secure the title, losing by way of a rear naked choke.<ref>{{cite web |title=Completed MMA Bout |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/116943-shooto-1st-round-2014-shinya-murofushi-vs-junji-sarumaru-ito |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> He won the next three fights by TKO and again challanged for the flyweight title, held at the time by [[Yoshitaka Naito]]. He lost by a unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yoshitaka Naito vs. Junji Ito |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/223216-shooto-the-comic-vol-1-yoshitaka-nobita-naito-vs-junji-sarumaru-ito |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn his only fight outside [[Shooto]], at WSOF Global Championship 2, he faced the undefeated [[Jarred Brooks]], losing in the second round by TKO.<ref>{{cite web |title=Junji Ito vs. Jarred Brooks |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/241562-wsof-global-championship-2-junji-sarumaru-ito-vs-jarred-brooks |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Returning to Shooto he accrued a 4-1-2 record, with the most notable fights being a decision win against the undefeated Ryosuke Honda,<ref>{{cite web |title=Junji Ito vs. Ryosuke Honda |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/396639-shooto-11-17-junji-sarumaru-ito-vs-ryosuke-honda|website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> and a draw against the future [[Shooto]] strawweight and [[ONE Championship]] flyweight champion [[Yosuke Saruta]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Yosuke Saruta vs. Junji Ito |url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/bouts/283691-shooto-yusuke-tobizaru-saruta-vs-junji-sarumaru-ito |website=Tapology |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n| draws= 2\n| nc= \n| ko-wins= 9\n| ko-losses= 2\n| sub-wins= 1\n| sub-losses= 3\n| dec-wins= 6\n| dec-losses= 3\n| dq-wins= \n| dq-losses= \n| other-wins= \n| other-losses= \n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n| {{draw}}Draw\n| align=center| 16-8-2\n| Michael Nakagawa\n| Draw (Split)\n| Shooto - 30th Anniversary Tour 7th Round\n| {{dts|2019|September|22}}\n| align=center| 3\n| align=center| 5:00\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{yes2}}Loss\n| align=center| 16-8-1\n| Ryosuke Honda\n| Technical Decision (Unanimous)\n| Shooto - Professional Shooto 11/17\n| {{dts|2018|November|17}}\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 0:17\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{yes2}}Loss\n| align=center| 15-8-1\n| Mijikai Nagai\n| Decision (Unanimous)\n| Shooto - Professional Shooto 5/13\n| {{dts|2018|May|13}}\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 5:00\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{no2}}Loss\n| align=center| 14-8-1\n| Itchaku Murata\n| KO (Punch)\n| Shooto - Professional Shooto 1/28\n| {{dts|2018|January|28}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:53\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{draw}}Draw\n| align=center| 14-7-1\n| [[Yosuke Saruta]]\n| Draw (Majority)\n| Shooto - Professional Shooto 1/29\n| {{dts|2017|January|29}}\n| align=center| 3\n| align=center| 5:00\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| \n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 14-7\n| Takahiro Kohori\n| TKO (Punches)\n| Shooto - Professional Shooto 11/12\n| {{dts|2016|November|12}}\n| a